><div class="ingredients-list"><div class="ingredients-list__content"><ul class="ingredients-list__group"></ul><h3 class="ingredients-list__group-title">For the pears</h3><ul class="ingredients-list__group"><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="750g golden caster sugar">750g golden caster sugar</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 cinnamon stick">1 cinnamon stick</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 strips lemon zest (use a potato peeler)">2 strips lemon zest (use a potato peeler)</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 star anise">1 <a href="/glossary/star-anise" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">star anise</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary"><article id="node-259861" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/star-anise"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/staranise.jpg?itok=Bo2FB4hu" width="100" height="100" alt="Star anise" title="Star anise has a strong anise flavour, with a liquorice-like aroma" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/star-anise">Star anise</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">star an-eese</span><p>Star anise is one of the central spices in Chinese cooking. It has a strong anise flavour, with…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 vanilla pod, split lengthways">1 vanilla pod, split lengthways</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="5 cloves">5 <a href="/glossary/clove" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">cloves</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-259651" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/clove"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/cloves.jpg?itok=Nqd1UYuO" width="100" height="100" alt="Cloves" title="Cloves can be used whole or ground to impart a strong sweet but spicy and peppery flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/clove">Clove</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">klo-ve</span><p>The dry, unopened flower bud of the tropical myrtle tree family used to flavour a wide variety…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="piece fresh root ginger, peeled and sliced">piece fresh root ginger, peeled and sliced</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="4 ripe pears, peeled">4 ripe <a href="/glossary/pear" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">pears</a>, peeled<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-259496" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/pear"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/pear.jpg?itok=8jnzLE04" width="100" height="100" alt="Pear" title="Like apples, to which they are related, pears come in thousands of varieties" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/pear">Pear</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">pair</span><p>Like apples, to which they are related, pears come in thousands of varieties, of which only a…</p> </article></span></li></ul><h3 class="ingredients-list__group-title">For the chocolate sauce</h3><ul class="ingredients-list__group"><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="200g good-quality dark chocolate">200g good-quality <a href="/glossary/dark-chocolate" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">dark chocolate</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-6674781" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/dark-chocolate"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/08/chocolate-soup.png?itok=PD1fSe_E" width="100" height="100" alt="Dark chocolate soup pots with double cream in spoons" title="Dark chocolate soup" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/dark-chocolate">Dark chocolate</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">dahk chok-lit</span><p>Dark chocolate means the shiny, dark-reddish brown treat produced from the cacao bean, theobroma…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="142ml double cream">142ml double cream</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="150ml full-fat milk">150ml full-fat <a href="/glossary/milk" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">milk</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-260691" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/milk"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/milk-resized.jpg?itok=z-tC0wLi" width="100" height="100" alt="" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/milk">Milk</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">mill-k</span><p>One of the most widely used ingredients, milk is often referred to as a complete food. While cow…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="pinch ground cinnamon">pinch ground cinnamon</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="vanilla ice cream, to serve">vanilla ice cream, to serve</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>In a pan big enough to hold the pears snugly, tip in all the ingredients except the pears. Half fill the pan with water and bring to the boil. Simmer for 10 mins to infuse, drop in pears, cover and gently poach for about 30 mins until soft. Turn off the heat and set aside. The pears can be poached up to 2 days ahead and kept in the poaching syrup in the fridge.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>To make the chocolate sauce, tip the chocolate into a heatproof bowl. Bring the cream, milk and cinnamon to the boil and pour over the chocolate. Stir until the chocolate has melted. To serve, drain the pears and, holding them by the stem, dip them in the chocolate sauce to completely cover. Serve each pear with a generous scoop of vanilla ice cream.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1188601200" class="text-style-alt">September 2007</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div><div class="recipe__tips"><div class="field field-name-field-bbcgf-tips field-type-entityreference field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><div class="view view-recipe-views view-id-recipe_views view-display-id-tips view-dom-id-82976da452a16ea7315f72a19eaa270e"><div class="view-content"><div class="carousel-tips__wrapper carousel"><div class="flexslider carousel-tips__elements" data-type="carousel-tips"><ul class="slides carousel-tips__slides"><li class="carousel-tips__single-slide "><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-content"><h3>Recipe Tip</h3><h4><span class="field-content">If you want to use a slow cooker...</span></h4><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-body show-more__content">Tip the sugar, spices, lemon zest, vanilla and ginger with 500ml of water into your slow cooker, cover and cook on High until the sugar has totally dissolved- about 15 mins. Add the pears, turn the heat to Low and cook for 2-3 hours until tender. They'll now keep for up to 2 days in their syrup. Make the chocolate sauce and serve according to step 2, above.</div></div></li><li class="carousel-tips__single-slide "><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-content"><h3>Recipe Tip</h3><h4><span class="field-content">Pears with pork</span></h4><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-body show-more__content">Throwing wedges of pear in with a roast pork
joint 20 mins before it’s ready. Serve the roasted
pears alongside the carved meat.</div></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-5970946" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/recipe/recipe-image/2016/07/tropical-rocky-road.jpg?itok=ZsEDxd4-" width="324" height="294" alt="Tropical rocky road" title="Tropical rocky road" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/tropical-rocky-road"> Tropical rocky road </a></h3><div class="push-item__ratings"><div class="clearfix fivestar-average-stars fivestar-average-text"><div class="fivestar-static-form-item"><div class="form-item form-type-item"><div class="field-main"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">5</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="on"></span></div></div></div></div><div class="description"><p class="fivestar-summary fivestar-summary-">(1<span class="rating-text"> rating</span>)</p></div></div></div></div></div> </article></li><li class=""><article id="node-4484991" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/us